    <section class="hero">
      <p class="hero__eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="hero__title">Building Africa's <em>intelligent</em> infrastructure.</h1>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="border-top: none; padding-top: 0;">
      <div class="case-study__content">
        <p>I build intelligent systems that make enterprises smarter — not on clean demo data, but on production databases with undocumented schemas, conflicting business logic, and columns that mean four different things depending on who entered the record.</p>

        <p>At AI Creative Solutions, I'm the lead engineer on platforms that replace fragmented legacy systems — Access databases, Excel workbooks, and manual accounting — with unified, AI-first operational platforms. The work spans schema archaeology (reverse-engineering 60+ undocumented tables from a 12-year-old system), bank-grade security retrofits (envelope encryption, blind indexes, RBAC with scope concealment over databases that previously stored passwords in plaintext), and live ERP integration against production SAP Business One and Openbravo environments.</p>

        <p>I've built AI agent architectures that query live enterprise databases in real time — not CSV snapshots — with governance layers that make it architecturally impossible for the system to fabricate a number. One system replaced a ~$100K/year CRM with 75+ purpose-built tables, 44 AI action tools, and a safety layer that parses and scopes every AI-generated query before it touches production data. Another reconciles multi-currency receivables to the penny against a human source of truth before any figure reaches a user.</p>

        <p>Before this, I spent a year at Steward Bank building revenue assurance dashboards and automating data extraction across billing systems. That taught me how real organisations actually use data — and how far the gap is between a model that works and a system that delivers correct answers every day.</p>

        <p>My research — a hybrid CNN-Transformer for crop disease detection under real field conditions — won Best Poster at IndabaX Zimbabwe 2026. I'll represent Zimbabwe at Deep Learning Indaba 2027. I was recently featured in ITU News as one of the people powering machine-learning solutions globally.</p>

        <p>I compete on Zindi as Zimbabwe's Ambassador, organising events, running competitions, and mentoring the next generation of African data practitioners. I write about technology and leadership for Right for Education, reaching audiences across Africa.</p>

        <h2>Technical range</h2>
        <p>Python, T-SQL, PostgreSQL, React, TypeScript, Express, Power BI, MindStudio, PyTorch, TensorFlow, YOLOv8, Drizzle ORM, SAP Business One (SQL Server), Openbravo (PostgreSQL), Azure cloud services. I work across the full stack — from database reverse-engineering to production frontend to AI agent orchestration.</p>

        <h2>Education and credentials</h2>
        <p>Completing my BSc in Data Science and Informatics at the University of Zimbabwe (August 2026). Microsoft Certified: Azure AI Engineer Associate, Azure Data Scientist Associate, Power BI Data Analyst Associate. McKinsey Forward Program alumnus. WorldQuant University Applied AI Lab graduate.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
